<entry valign="top" align="center" namest="c1" nameend="c2"><emphasis effect="bold">Unit 7: Chapter 15 (1968–1980)</emphasis></entry>
</row>
<row valign="top">
<entry valign="top" align="left" namest="c1" nameend="c2"><emphasis effect="bold">Compelling Question: How did a fracturing of the liberal consensus shape politics and culture between 1968 and 1980?</emphasis></entry>
</row>
<row valign="top">
<entry valign="top" align="left" namest="c1" nameend="c2"><emphasis effect="bold">Chapter Objectives:</emphasis>
<list id="fs-idm225726320" list-type="bulleted">
<item>Students will explain the triumph and decline of the liberal consensus over the welfare state and the rise of the conservative movement.</item>
<item>Students will analyze how different groups in American society fought for equality and rights.</item></list></entry>
</row>
